beer.beer_description: Indoor Plant Sale is a redux of one of our favourite IPAs of yesteryear. This opaque, golden ale features bright, pithy citrus aromas mixed with fresh passionfruit and grapefruit thanks to a generous dip hopping of Strata, and heavy dry hopping of Centennial and, once again,  Strata (its like its one of our brewers favourite hops). Fusing with that modern East-Coast style we've decided to smack this beer with a classic West-Coast bitterness which finishes off the palate with notes of spruce-pine, resin, and just a touch of weedy dankness.  Top it all off with a thicc meringue-like foam and we reckon we created the perfect hybrid IPA showing off the best of both coasts.
